Mokgweetsi Masisi Sign up here for our daily coronavirus newsletter on what you need to know, and subscribe to our Covid-19 podcast for the latest news and analysis. Botswana President Mokgweetsi Masisi started 14 days of quarantine after an official tested positive for coronavirus. The president started the quarantine Wednesday night after “an official closely serving him” tested positive for the virus, according to a statement emailed by the Office of the President. This is the fourth time that Masisi has had to go into quarantine since the southern African country recorded its first Covid-19 case on March 30. Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter